{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "648b5a64417cc3fb48d65edd", "type": "singleCorrect", "level": 2, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": 120, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "EM", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76b2c52ffa3c944600df"], "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eb9e"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "microConcepts": [], "questionLabels": [], "previousYearPapers": [{"_id": "648b5a3a0d9d0b909f7b6487", "title": "JEE Main 2015 (04 Apr)", "isVisible": true}], "question": {"text": "<p>A rectangular loop of sides <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>, carrying a current <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>I</mi></math> of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>12</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math>, is placed in different orientations as shown in the figure below.<br />(a) <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/P_41_Option_1.jpg\" style=\"width: 180px; height: 134px;\" />&nbsp;(b) <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/P_41_Option_2.jpg\" style=\"width: 180px; height: 134px;\" /><br /><br />(c) <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/P_41_Option_3.jpg\" style=\"width: 180px; height: 133px;\" />&nbsp;(d) <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/P_41_Option_4.jpg\" style=\"width: 180px; height: 131px;\" /></p><p>If there is a uniform magnetic field of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></math> in the positive <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>z</mi></math> direction, in which orientations the loop would be in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>)</mo></math> stable equilibrium and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi>ii</mi><mo>)</mo></math> unstable equilibrium?</p>", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "m2uKi", "text": "(b) and (c), respectively.", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "fIzPZ", "text": "(a) and (b), respectively.", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "FTPax", "text": "(a) and (c), respectively.", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "557Zb", "text": "(b) and (d), respectively.", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "<p>For a magnetic dipole placed in a uniform magnetic field, the torque is given by <math><mover accent=\"true\"><mrow><mi>&#964;</mi></mrow><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mover accent=\"true\"><mrow><mi>M</mi></mrow><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>&#215;</mo><mover accent=\"true\"><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover></math>, and potential energy <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>U</mi></math> is given as,<br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>U</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>M</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>&#183;</mo><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>B</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>M</mi><mi>B</mi><mi>cos</mi><mi>&#952;</mi></math><br /><br />When <math><mover accent=\"true\"><mrow><mi>M</mi></mrow><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover></math> is in the same direction as <math><mover accent=\"true\"><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover></math> then <math><mover accent=\"true\"><mrow><mi>&#964;</mi></mrow><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>U</mi></math> is minimum = <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mi>M</mi><mi>B</mi></math> as <math><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>o</mi></mrow></msup></math>.<math><mo>&#8658;</mo></math> Stable equilibrium is (b).</p><p>When <math><mover accent=\"true\"><mrow><mi>M</mi></mrow><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover></math> the opposite direction of <math><mover accent=\"true\"><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover></math>, then <math><mover accent=\"true\"><mrow><mi>&#964;</mi></mrow><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>U</mi></math> is max = <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>+</mo><mi>M</mi><mi>B</mi></math><br />As,&nbsp;<math><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mrow><mn>180</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>o</mi></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo></math>Unstable equilibrium in (d)</p>", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "masterId": "MOGJMPYQ76156196", "numericalLowerLimit": null, "numericalUpperLimit": null, "bucket": "", "isRemoved": false, "cpyqbSubjects": ["61bb58181213731910ea0b70", "61c055eae8ce0dc8a5c62d33", "616057750283de43c87e3e1b", "61964fe0a5a5260118868021", "61964f81a5a526011886801d", "629f39e4ac11b26562e0625b", "616057920283de43c87e3e1e", "615f0c729476412f48314dab", "61a8a2c2e8ce0dc8a5c62d2d", "629105adee9e3ae00d63352b", "629f385f263330a77be9fa7d", "616056cd0283de43c87e3e15", "616057190283de43c87e3e18", "62962075e7f8e9ac4daeafd7", "64d50bd73df7f4a7f3017f6f", "66b79b34d4b564dfab4f94cc", "678ea9a09cc79e5f592bdc11", "67fa5fef4468eb1307ceb0ad", "6807d2ad647479b8e8696479"], "cpyqbChapters": ["61602420ae6dd863a9d1d7d8", "6160241f1a832a8dea12fbf0", "616024236098c3dc0cc3e764", "61602422b42cfaef18219875", "616024227e2ba4496fdd4552", "61964c8c8d7ade9f02022966", "61c08987636555dc34527e11", "61e7bd70643383b6c26bfb1d", "61964c8e8811f774a40dd9f1", "62962123b040395dcc21a751", "629f3a9143c2c00ea1d2f857", "629109edc3391b7808eb05af", "61bb820fdb486fa25580e4bd", "629